name: nitrite reductase (NADH)
classes: Acting on other nitrogenous compounds as donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: NH3 + 3 NAD+ + 2 H2O = nitrite + 3 NADH + 5 H+ [RN:R00787]
comment: An iron-sulfur flavoprotein (FAD) containing siroheme. This prokaryotic enzyme is specific for NADH. In addition to catalysing the 6-electron reduction of nitrite to ammonia, the enzyme from Escherichia coli can also catalyse the 2-electron reduction of hydroxylamine to ammonia. cf. EC 1.7.1.4, nitrite reductase [NAD(P)H].
